            "content": "I created a simple Node.js HTTP server file (server.js) and attempted to run it in the sandbox, but starting processes failed in this environment. Below are the server code, exact commands to run and test it with curl on your machine, and the expected curl response.\n\n1) server.js\n```js\nconst http = require('http');\nconst port = process.env.PORT || 3000;\n\nconst server = http.createServer((req, res) => {\n  res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'text/plain' });\n  res.end('Hello from Node.js server!\\n');\n});\n\nserver.listen(port, () => {\n  console.log(`Server running on port ${port}`);\n});\n```\n\n2) How to run and test locally\n\n- Start the server:\n  - macOS / Linux:\n    - node server.js\n    - or run in background: node server.js & 
